  "text": "## Comprehensive SSO Settings API Feature Flag Control Flow\n\n### Layer 1: Feature Flag Definition\n\nThe `ssoSettingsApi` feature flag is defined as a General Availability (GA) feature in `pkg/services/featuremgmt/registry.go` (line 934-941) with Expression='true' and AllowSelfServe=true. This definition is automatically code-generated into:\n\n1. **Go Constants** (`pkg/services/featuremgmt/toggles_gen.go`): Generated constant `FlagSsoSettingsApi` used throughout backend code\n2. **TypeScript Types** (`packages/grafana-data/src/types/featureToggles.gen.ts`): Generated optional boolean property `ssoSettingsApi` in the FeatureToggles interface for frontend consumption\n\n### Layer 2: SSO Settings Infrastructure\n\nThe feature flag gates the entire SSO settings infrastructure layer:\n\n**Service Interface** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettings.go`):\n- `Service` interface: Core methods for List, Get, Upsert, Delete SSO settings, RegisterReloadable\n- `Reloadable` interface: Allows providers (OAuth, LDAP, SAML) to validate and reload settings when updated\n- `Store` interface: Abstract database operations\n- `FallbackStrategy` interface: Provides backwards compatibility for config file settings\n\n**Data Model** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/models/models.go`):\n- `SSOSettings` struct with xorm ORM annotations, mapped to `sso_setting` database table\n- Settings stored as JSON with automatic snake_case ↔ camelCase conversion\n- Source tracking (DB vs System) for audit purposes\n\n**Database Layer** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/database/database.go`):\n- `SSOSettingsStore` implementing the Store interface\n- Soft-delete support via `is_deleted` column\n- CRUD operations: Get, List, Upsert (with insert or update), Delete\n\n**Service Implementation** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettingsimpl/service.go`):\n- `ProvideService` function is the main DI entry point (lines 47-100)\n- **Critical Gate**: Line 94-96 checks `features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi)`\n  - If enabled: Creates and registers API endpoints via `api.ProvideApi(svc, routeRegister, ac).RegisterAPIEndpoints()`\n  - If disabled: API endpoints are NOT registered\n- Wires fallback strategies (OAuth, LDAP, SAML) based on licensing and flags\n- Manages reloadables for live configuration updates\n\n### Layer 3: API & Authentication Wiring\n\nThe feature flag controls how OAuth and authentication providers are wired:\n\n**REST API Endpoints** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/api/api.go`):\n- Route group: `/api/v1/sso-settings` (line 63)\n- Only registered when FlagSsoSettingsApi is enabled\n- Endpoints:\n  - `GET /api/v1/sso-settings`: List all provider settings (read permission)\n  - `GET /api/v1/sso-settings/:key`: Get specific provider settings (read permission per provider scope)\n  - `PUT /api/v1/sso-settings/:key`: Update provider settings (write permission per provider scope)\n  - `DELETE /api/v1/sso-settings/:key`: Delete provider settings (write permission per provider scope)\n- Uses `ac.ScopeSettingsOAuth(provider)` for per-provider access control\n\n**OAuth Connector Loading** (`pkg/login/social/socialimpl/service.go`, lines 56-81):\n- **When enabled**: Loads all OAuth settings from SSO settings service (`ssoSettings.List()`), creates OAuthConnector instances from database-persisted settings\n- **When disabled**: Falls back to reading from INI config files (`cfg.Raw.Section(\"auth.\" + name)`)\n- This dual-path ensures backwards compatibility\n\n**LDAP Authentication Registration** (`pkg/services/authn/authnimpl/registration.go`, line 56):\n- LDAP is registered if `(cfg.LDAPAuthEnabled OR (FlagSsoSettingsApi AND FlagSsoSettingsLDAP))`\n- When both flags enabled, LDAP is managed via SSO settings service instead of config file\n\n**LDAP Reloadable Registration** (`pkg/services/ldap/service/ldap.go`, line 59-60):\n- When `FlagSsoSettingsApi && FlagSsoSettingsLDAP`, LDAP service registers itself as a Reloadable\n- Allows hot-reload of LDAP configuration through SSO settings service\n\n**Admin Routes & Access Control** (`pkg/api/api.go`, lines 231-244):\n- `adminAuthPageEvaluator` function combines authentication setting evaluators\n- When FlagSsoSettingsApi enabled: Includes OAuth settings evaluator from all configurable providers\n- Route `/admin/authentication`: Guarded by combined evaluator\n- Route `/admin/authentication:provider`: Only available when FlagSsoSettingsApi enabled\n\n### Layer 4: Access Control & DI Registration\n\nThe feature flag gates admin visibility and API access:\n\n**Access Control Evaluators** (`pkg/services/accesscontrol/ssoutils/utils.go`):\n- `EvalAuthenticationSettings()`: Evaluates permissions for SAML and LDAP settings\n- `OauthSettingsEvaluator()`: Evaluates read/write permissions for each OAuth provider based on `cfg.SSOSettingsConfigurableProviders`\n- Uses scope pattern `settings:auth.<provider>:*` for granular RBAC\n\n**Admin Navigation** (`pkg/services/navtree/navtreeimpl/admin.go`, lines 184-194):\n- 'Authentication' admin nav link is shown when:\n  - `authConfigUIAvailable AND hasAccess(EvalAuthenticationSettings)` OR\n  - `hasAccess(OauthSettingsEvaluator) AND FlagSsoSettingsApi`\n- Appears in admin config section only with appropriate permissions\n\n**Frontend LDAP Registration** (`public/app/features/auth-config/index.ts`, line 56):\n- `initAuthConfig()`: If `config.featureToggles.ssoSettingsApi && ssoSettingsLDAP`, skips registering LDAP in legacy auth provider system\n- LDAP is then managed through the new SSO settings API instead\n\n**Frontend API Calls** (`public/app/features/auth-config/state/actions.ts`, line 40-42):\n- `loadProviders()` thunk checks `!config.featureToggles.ssoSettingsApi`\n- If disabled: Returns empty array (no SSO settings API calls)\n- If enabled: Calls `/api/v1/sso-settings` endpoint\n\n**Frontend Routes** (`public/app/routes/routes.tsx`, lines 286 & 304):\n- `/admin/authentication` route shows `AuthProvidersListPage` if ssoSettingsApi enabled\n- `/admin/authentication/:provider` route shows `ProviderConfigPage` only when ssoSettingsApi enabled\n- Both routes render `<Navigate replace to=\"/admin\" />` when feature disabled\n\n### Control Flow Summary\n\nThe `ssoSettingsApi` feature flag creates a **complete control gate** across all four layers:\n\n1. **Definition**: Feature flag defined as GA in registry, generated to Go/TS constants\n2. **Infrastructure**: Entire SSO settings service, database schema, and reloadable system only instantiated when flag enabled\n3. **API Wiring**: REST endpoints, OAuth connector loading, LDAP authentication, and hot-reload capabilities conditional on flag\n4. **Access Control**: Admin UI visibility, route access, API endpoint access, and navigation all gated through flag checks\n\nThis implements the **principle of complete gating**: when the flag is disabled, users cannot see, access, or utilize SSO settings management capabilities. When enabled, full end-to-end control is available through:\n- Database-backed configuration storage (vs. file-based fallback)\n- Live hot-reload of authentication providers\n- Granular per-provider RBAC via access control evaluators\n- Admin UI for OAuth/LDAP configuration\n- API-first architecture for programmatic settings management"
